@@eThe Cinderteeth -- As Kowloon Sees It@@N

@@rTemple Circle Memorial Registry, Ashfall Division@@N

No region cuts deeper into Kowloon's memory than the @@rCinderteeth@@N.
Those broken volcanic ridges are why this city exists. They are why
six hundred souls drowned in Yen-Mak. They are why we ink the
@@yNeon Covenant@@N in phosphorescent squid dye. Every institution we
have was forged in the aftermath of what those mountains did to us.

The @@rAshfall Monsoon@@N was not a single event. Three years of black
volcanic rain choked our canals, collapsed roofs, turned fresh water
to sulfur. Kowloon's delta -- low, wet, open to the sky -- caught
the worst. The ash did not merely fall. It @@drained@@N, mixing with
water to become poison in every channel of the @@dShallow Thousand@@N.

The Temple Circle maintains the @@dAshfall Registry@@N: six hundred names
from Yen-Mak, plus the uncounted dead from years one and two. Every
autumn during the @@dAshfall Vigil@@N, those names are spoken aloud in
darkness. The Executioner strikes the covenant stone three times.
This is not ceremony. It is @@rpractice against forgetting@@N.

The Jade Magistracy funds observers at the @@WChalkwind Saddles@@N who
report tremor frequency and gas color. The @@yVentspeakers@@N -- highland
people who read volcanic vents as practical geology -- have our
respect. When the @@rAsh Cult@@N claims eruptions are divine verdicts,
the Temple Circle replies: @@y"Verdicts do not drown children."@@N

The @@WSpirebound Conclave@@N embedded @@lresonance crystals@@N in the
Bellspine ridge and abandoned them. The Courier Lantern Office marks
this as @@rinstitutional negligence@@N -- instruments left running
without keepers, potentially amplifying the seismic coupling that
drove our Ashfall. We do not forgive this.

The @@ySilent Bell Protocol@@N and @@rDouble-water doctrine@@N are mountain
law, but Kowloon adopted both for harbor emergency codes. When the
bay bells ring a certain pattern, every dock crew knows: @@rstop,
separate, do not share water@@N. We learned this from the dead.

Six subregions fill our @@rhazard registry@@N: the @@rEmber Crown@@N of
active calderas, the @@dBellspine@@N where abandoned crystals ring, the
@@WChalkwind Saddles@@N where our observers stand, the @@yGlasswash Fans@@N
of obsidian and sulfur, the @@gBlackstep Footholds@@N where mountain
meets civic law, and the @@lWestern Fold@@N of smoldering Conclave ruins.

The mountains are not finished. The deep fault runs beneath the
continent. The Jade Magistracy's standing order is simple:
@@ywatch the mountains, always@@N.
